Introduction¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset contains the details of 183412 rows with 16 attributes, most variables are numeric in nature.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The main features of interest are: gender, user type, duration_sec, start_hour, age and stations

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I thinks the feature that will support my investigation are duration_sec and user_type

# create column of day of the week
CleanFord_bike['day_of_week'] = pd.DatetimeIndex(CleanFord_bike['start_time']).strftime('%A')
# create column of the time of the day
CleanFord_bike['start_hour'] = CleanFord_bike['start_time'].apply(lambda time: time.hour)
CleanFord_bike['time_of_day'] = 'Morning'
CleanFord_bike['time_of_day'][(CleanFord_bike['start_hour'] >= 12) & (CleanFord_bike['start_hour'] <= 17)] = 'Afternoon'
CleanFord_bike['time_of_day'][(CleanFord_bike['start_hour'] >= 18) & (CleanFord_bike['start_hour'] <= 23)] = 'Night'

locs, labels = plt.xticks()

# print frequency on the bar chart
for loc, label in zip(locs, labels):

    pct_string = '{:0.1f}%'.format(100*count/n_points)
